<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-13T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="613" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d613">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500. A 4e/16: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-13T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 13,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your 3 April 7, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <p>For Arnold.</p>
                        <p>Department’s view is that any basis of valuation would be acceptable
                            which in the judgment of the Revision Commission is deemed to correspond
                            most nearly with the actual values which may be anticipated to prevail
                            pending the further revision contemplated by Article 4 of the Customs
                            Convention concluded February 6th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
